title: Mammograms may reveal hidden heart risks for women, Penn State study finds
description: Routine mammograms are best known as a front-line tool for detecting breast cancer. But new research suggests the same X-ray images may also offer an early warning sign for cardiovascular disease — the leading cause of death among women.
